The paper deals with the trade-off between information complexity and error in communication protocols, which is a topic that falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the analysis of communication complexity for specific functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of entropy functions suggests a connection to information theory and probability theory, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
